ASABA- Delta State Government yesterday flagged off Covid-19 Mass Vaccination Campaign in the state capital, Asaba. Speaking during the flag of Covid-19 vaccination at Asaba Specialist Hospital, Commissioner of Health, Dr Mordi Ononye who represented the Governor urged Deltans to disabuse their minds towards myths associated with the vaccine. According to Ononye, “Since ages past, all of us have been exposed to one form of vaccination it the other. We all have scars on our hands from small pox vaccination.” HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Vaccines are brought forth as a way to fight communicable disease. It has been so at all times, so why can this one be different. There is a notion that something demonic has been embedded in the vaccine to monitor people but that is not true”. Strong-arm Tactics, Distortions Will Not Resolve Minimum Wage Logjam-DG PGF Okowa Congratulates NFF President, Amaju Pinnick On FIFA Seat Victory Earlier while recalling the monstrous effect of Covid-19 on the global economy, Chairman of Delta State Primary HealthCare Agency ( DSPHCA), Dr Isioma Okoba described the emergence of the vaccine as a breathe of fresh air sufferings of the masses. She warned that Covid-19 precautionary measures should not be ignored despite vaccination, saying that even if you have been vaccinated you cannot throw caution into the wind.